<plot>A cartoon in the Paramount audience-participation, follow-the-bouncing-ball sing-along series (Paramount number X7-3)in which it shows that blowing the apples off a tree with an electric fan works so well that the old cider mill breaks down from an overload, and the cider in the old-mill stream has an odd effect on all the animals in the vicinity. A cow gives 100-proof milk and a fisherman's hook catches fish by their tail.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?337945</url></doc>
